Name: OPDTRIAGE
Description: OPD Triage information for vital signs and initial assessment

Name: ORDER
Description: Used for lab and drug orders

Name: CHECKIN
Description: Indicates the patient has done the required paperwork and check-in to begin a visit to the clinic/hospital.

Name: ADMISSION
Description: Indicates that the patient has been admitted for inpatient care, and is not expected to leave the hospital unless discharged.

Name: DISCHARGE
Description: Indicates that a patient's inpatient care at the hospital is ending, and they are expected to leave soon.

Name: TRANSFERREQUEST
Description: A stand-alone encounter type for a transfer request not part of a larger note

Name: INPATIENTNOTE
Description: A short free-text note written by a clinician about an inpatient during their stay

Name: BEDASSIGNMENT
Description: Assigning a new bed to a patient without admitting or transferring them

Name: CANCELADT
Description: An encounter that notes that a request to admit/transfer/discharge a patient is being overridden

Name: NCDINITIAL
Description: To be used in filling the NCD enrollement form.
